    "cultural_note": "After the 1997 handover, Hongkong Post repainted its red colonial postboxes green, but around 59 of the old cast-iron boxes, made in the UK with royal cyphers, are still in service. Look closely: some bear EIIR (Elizabeth II), some GRVI (George VI), some GRV (George V). The boxes were never swapped out between monarchs, so the whole history of the colonial period is still sitting on street corners, holding letters.",
